description: Despite the cover saying "U.K. edition", there was no other version of this comic. Instead Scion deliberately tried to mimic the style of imported U.S. superhero titles, hoping to make an inroad into that market.
Translates Deadpool #25-26 and Deadpool Team-Up #89.

Includes the strips:

Speeding Through Space

The Death Daring Duvals

Atomic Tommy and the Bullet-Proof Crime.

description: Holyoke Comics top costumed crimefighter of the Golden Age returns in a pair of beautifully reprinted stories featuring the Feline Fury and his youthful aid, Kitten. “Larceny in Liquid”, with art by Charles Quinlan is from Catman Comics #20, and involves one of the Cat’s two top adversaries- Mr. Peccary. The second story, (untitled) comes from Catman #30, and is drawn by the great Bob Fujitani. It features our hero’s other great opponent, Dr. Macabre, wherin the good doctor teams up with two larcenous and mad sisters, and a team of murderous, trained gorillas. Also, you get an Alan Mandel-drawn adventure of the costumed crimefighter known only as The Hood. It originally saw print in Catman Comics #20. Color cover by fan-favorite L. B. Cole, it also has a frontis sketch by Brad Gorby. Interiors are black and white with graytones.

name: The Return of the Sky Band
